race.comment: PETTICOAT (3) progressive Coffs Harbour mare who returns from a let-up. Demolished a Highway field with the 60kg in fast time over 1000m at this track. Since fitted with a sharp 810m trial win and should have little trouble running out the 1100m from the good draw. COLUMBIA BLUE (2) lightly raced gelding going quickly through the grades. Strong through the line from the outside gate when saluting over 1100m at Canterbury. Steps up a level and the 3kg claim keeps him in the mix. SCAMPI (1) shouldered the 61kg first-up when a fast finishing second over 1100m at Ballarat. In-form apprentice hops aboard and look for him launching late. ICE KOOL (12) created a big impression as fav on debut when a slick 3.5 len winner over 1000m at Warwick Farm in a Super Mdn. Hard to have at the price. BENEVAC (10) next best.
